Description: Gibson ES-137 Classic Triburst (figured) 2009 in very good condition. No cracks, breaks or repairs. All electronics function correctly. Truss rod functions correctly. Some finish wear on face, sides and back, including some light hazing; some minor dings on face (including under pickguard), sides and back (pictured). Gold plating worn on tailpiece. Back of neck very clean. Neck joint perfect (with some finish checking; pictured). Frets show some wear. Minor button rash on back; no buckle rash. Replacement pickguard and bracket; pickguard shows scratching. Replacement gold speed knobs; original black speed knobs in case pocket. Otherwise no modifications. Certificate of Authenticity included. Original hardshell case in good condition is functional but retaining strap has separated from the case bottom and one latch is broken. Currently set up with Thomastik JS113s) (flatwounds). Youtube link to instrument as used in tune Mr. Clean: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sLnrMqhWkYQ. Shipping to continental United States only.
